23 25-1-1303. State entities prohibited from assisting federal agencies
24 collecting electronic data or metadata.
25 The state or a state agency shall not assist, participate with, or
26 provide material support or resources to enable a United States Government
27 agency in the collection or use of a person's electronic data or metadata,
28 unless one (1) or more of the following apply:
29 (1) The person has given informed consent; or
30 (2) The collection or use of the electronic data or metadata is:
31 (A) Pursuant to a warrant that:
32 (i) Is based upon reasonable cause; and
33 (ii) Describes with particularity the person, place,
34 or thing to be searched or seized; or
35 (B) According to a legally recognized exception to the
36 warrant requirement.
